The rapier is a light, thrusting sword popular among nobles and swashbucklers. Often associated with dueling and sport fighting, rapiers are nonetheless deadly in trained hands.

This particular rapier is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The scimitar shares some similarities with the longsword and other slashing blades, but the severity and thickness of its curve clearly sets it apart. 

This particular scimitar is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

Bastard swords are also known as hand-and-a-half swords, falling between the longsword and greatsword in length.This is a particularly well-made example.

One of the first types of sword to come into existence, the short sword is a double-edged weapon about two feet long. It is an economical weapon, and a favorite of archers and rogues.

Derived from a farm implement used for threshing grain, the heavy flail consists of a four-foot wooden shaft attached to a heavy or spiked head by a chain or hinge. 

This particular heavy flail is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

Originally a farm implement for threshing grain, the light flail consists of a wooden shaft attached to a heavy or spiked head by a chain or hinge. The light flail is approximately two feet long.

This particular light flail is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The light hammer is derived from commonly used mining tools. It remains small enough to still be used in excavation, unlike the much heavier warhammer. 

This particular light hammer is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The mace is a derivative of the basic club, consisting of a stone or metal head mounted on the end of a wooden shaft. The weight of the head greatly increases the force of impact.

This particular mace is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The morningstar is a derivative of the mace that includes a chain tether - similar to the flail - to add velocity when swinging its compact striking surface. Morningstars commonly have at least one formidable spike as an added feature of the head. This one is particularly well-crafted.

Whatever can be said of the orc race, there is no doubting the impact they have had on warfare. The orc double axe is a perfect example, patterned after their "One blade good, two blades better!" wisdom.

This particular double axe is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The two-bladed sword is a marriage of concepts forged on the battlefield, combining the quickness and versatility of the quarterstaff with the edged effectiveness of two fearsome blades.

This particular two bladed sword is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The dire mace is an attempt to combine the versatility of the quarterstaff with the striking power of the mace. 

This particular dire mace is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The sickle is a farming implement used for cutting grass and grains. Like many other such tools, it was adapted for use as a weapon by the peasants familiar with it in their daily toils.

This particular sickle is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The halberd is the most common polearm, and could be called a cross between a spear and an axe. Such weapons are often mass-produced for militia, and serve well when defending against marauders. This one, however, is particularly well-made.

Another of history's most basic weapons, the spear is nevertheless a formidable weapon. Little more that a simple shaft topped with a sharpened head, the spear is the staple of many a militia. This, however, is a particularly well-made example.
